OL,6,F"I'm pleased for Geoffrey's loved ones
OL,7,Fwe have now managed to bring them some
OL,8,Fclosure and justice to this ordeal,
OL,9,Fand our condolences as a force remain
OL,10,Fwith them as they still come to terms
OL,11,Fwith their loss.
OL,13,FGeoffry Ives' family also paid this
OL,14,Ftribute: "He has been there and
OL,15,Fsupported us throughout our whole
OL,16,Flives, always putting us first.
OL,18,F"He was a stubborn man, but there
OL,19,Fwasn't a bad bone in his body.
OL,20,FEveryone that knew him loved him.
